Environmentalists are trying to use such a listing to force the United States to restrict heat-trapping gases scientists have linked to global warming as a way of limiting risks to the 22,000 or so bears in the far north.
Department of Interior Secretary Dirk Kempthorne in December proposed listing bears as a "threatened" species instead.
The Fish and Wildlife Service is taking public comments on listing until April 9.
The Marine Mammal Protection Act imposes a general moratorium on the taking of marine mammals.
